most loyal subject.

165
00:14:36,022 --> 00:14:39,731
Welcome home, Mr. Raleigh.
Lord Howard, the docks.

166
00:14:40,470 --> 00:14:42,476
Master Raleigh.

167
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:48,403
You eat it...

168
00:15:10,260 --> 00:15:12,268
You traitor!

169
00:15:12,565 --> 00:15:14,158
Judas!

170
00:15:14,773 --> 00:15:16,682
You're Walsingham's pawn!

171
00:15:17,716 --> 00:15:20,368
Don't do this!
I didn't say anything!

172
00:15:21,301 --> 00:15:23,885
You're a
Protestant traitor!

173
00:15:24,788 --> 00:15:26,349
Don't do it! Don't!

174
00:15:36,084 --> 00:15:37,261
Don't!
Hold his head!

175
00:15:37,332 --> 00:15:39,754
You Judas! You Judas!
Stop!

176
00:15:39,827 --> 00:15:41,104
You Judas!

177
00:16:07,123 --> 00:16:09,873
The traitor's dead.
We must act!

178
00:16:14,163 --> 00:16:17,458
Why do we not strike?
What are we waiting for?

179
00:16:20,403 --> 00:16:23,336
You wait for my order.

180
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:30,926
Walsingham knows
too much already.
One traitor is dead.

181
00:16:31,698 --> 00:16:34,546
Who can I trust now?

182
00:16:41,522 --> 00:16:43,823
There's a visitor
waiting, sir.

183
00:16:48,370 --> 00:16:50,573
William.

184
00:16:52,562 --> 00:16:54,448
Hello, Francis.

185
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:57,863
You've always
been a fellow who
delighted in surprises.

186
00:16:57,937 --> 00:16:59,759
You look well,
Francis.

187
00:16:59,856 --> 00:17:03,687
Well, you look dreadful.
They're not feeding
you in Paris.

188
00:17:03,793 --> 00:17:07,087
You can't learn
the secrets of the universe
on an empty stomach.

189
00:17:07,569 --> 00:17:11,246
<i>Then she my heart beguiled</i>

190
00:17:11,314 --> 00:17:15,590
Mary. William.
Supper is ready.

191
00:17:17,361 --> 00:17:19,019
William.

192
00:17:19,088 --> 00:17:20,518
Have you spoken
to the Queen?

193
00:17:20,593 --> 00:17:21,673
I speak
with the Queen daily.

194
00:17:21,744 --> 00:17:23,598
You work too hard.
You're a sick man.

195
00:17:23,664 --> 00:17:25,224
William,
come over here
and sit by me.

196
00:17:25,297 --> 00:17:26,638
William, if we are not
allowed to sin,

197
00:17:26,704 --> 00:17:27,849
maybe we could
talk theology.

198
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:30,702
You have done enough.
No man could do more.

199
00:17:30,768 --> 00:17:32,906
I can't leave
the court yet, Ursula.
She needs me.

200
00:17:32,977 --> 00:17:34,602
Never listens to me.
Not a thought for his health.

201
00:17:34,672 --> 00:17:36,013
So you talk to him,
he's your brother.

202
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:39,822
William, what do they say
in Paris about the Pope's
call for holy war?

203
00:17:39,887 --> 00:17:40,869
Many welcome it.

204
00:17:40,943 --> 00:17:42,602
Why must we talk
about war?

205
00:17:42,672 --> 00:17:44,777
Tell us your nice
news, William.

206
00:17:44,847 --> 00:17:46,887
Are you married yet?
Not yet.

207
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:49,131
Mary, would you leave
William alone, please?

208
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,851
Sweet, sit.

209
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:54,279
Grace?

210
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,348
Oh, Lord,
provider of all things,

211
00:17:57,423 --> 00:17:59,333
we offer Thee
our humble thanks.

212
00:17:59,407 --> 00:18:02,190
In the name
of the Holy Trinity, amen.

213
00:18:02,255 --> 00:18:03,335
Amen.

214
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:14,726
More lines on my face.

215
00:18:16,878 --> 00:18:18,919
Where do they come from?

216
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:21,030
Smile lines, my lady.

217
00:18:21,103 --> 00:18:23,306
Smile lines?

218
00:18:24,398 --> 00:18:27,017
When do I ever smile?

219
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:32,424
Now you have
smile lines, too.

220
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:43,148
<i>The beauty of Your Majesty</i>

221
00:18:43,213 --> 00:18:47,403
<i>is dazzling to my eyes.</i>

222
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:58,278
I am overwhelmed.

223
00:18:58,349 --> 00:19:01,644
I am conquered.

224
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:04,164
I die.

225
00:19:04,238 --> 00:19:07,140
Only your love,

226
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:09,733
<i>my stattlich Elizabeth,</i>

227
00:19:09,805 --> 00:19:11,845
can restore me into life.

228
00:19:12,941 --> 00:19:15,875
Your Highness
does me great honor.

229
00:19:24,173 --> 00:19:26,278
Oh, Elizabeth.

230
00:19:26,509 --> 00:19:31,625
How blessed am I
to stand in your
fabled presence.

231
00:19:32,876 --> 00:19:35,266
Ah, Elizabeth.

232
00:19:35,339 --> 00:19:37,511
To speak your name
is to hear celestial music.

233
00:19:41,163 --> 00:19:44,512
May that sweet sound

234
00:19:44,587 --> 00:19:48,231
guide me through my life
to come, Elizabeth.

235
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:53,892
I have traveled here
to this illustrious court

236
00:19:54,092 --> 00:19:57,866
in the hope that
our two great nations

237
00:19:59,115 --> 00:20:01,416
might be
joined in love.

238
00:20:14,987 --> 00:20:16,775
He interests me.

239
00:20:18,954 --> 00:20:20,930
Talk to him.

240
00:20:21,002 --> 00:20:24,068
Him, my lady?

241
00:20:24,138 --> 00:20:25,250
Him.

242
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:33,541
I adore the natives
you brought. I don't suppose
you could get one for me.

243
00:20:33,611 --> 00:20:34,984
They're not
dangerous, are they?

244
00:20:35,049 --> 00:20:36,806
That depends
on what you propose
to do with them.

245
00:20:36,874 --> 00:20:39,240
I'd dress him up
in mulberry
colored silk,

246
00:20:39,306 --> 00:20:42,121
and have him walk
behind me,
carrying my cloak.

247
00:20:49,961 --> 00:20:52,262
I have a secret,
my dear.

248
00:20:54,026 --> 00:20:56,546
I pretend there's
a pane of glass,

249
00:20:56,616 --> 00:21:00,413
